cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper investigates the role of recurrent connections in aiding object recognition, specifically in the context of occluded objects. This topic is highly relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also compares different architectures and evaluates performance, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper analyzes how the network's representation of stimuli evolves over time, which could be considered natural language processing (cs.CL) in the context of understanding how the network processes and interprets visual information.
